<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In file library/Zend/Auth/Adapter/Http.php, revision from 2008-07-18:12:08 GMT +1</p>

<p>Line 751:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
  if ($rUri['path'] != urldecode($cUri['path'])) {
    return false;
  }
</code></pre>

<p>should be changed to:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
  if ($rUri['path'] != $cUri['path']) {
    return false;
  }
</code></pre>

<p>Looks like there is code that already is taking care to urlencode $rUri['path'] so there is no need
for $cUri['path'] to be decoded.</p>

<p>Please close also bug report:
<a href="http://framework.zend.com/issues/browse/ZF-3066">http://framework.zend.com/issues/browse/ZF-3066</a></p>

<p>Since it's no longer valid for the latest SVN version of the adapter.</p>

